        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="749" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d749">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/11–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-18">November 18,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 18—4:40 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2464. Following received from Mukden, 4 p. m., 18th:</p>
                <p>“Mukden radio station now closing down and will not reopen as it is in process
                    being seized. Inform Department, Embassy soonest. Ward.”</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2464; repeated Nanking 1863.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
